-- Chelsea Makes First Profit Since Abramovich Became Owner in 2003
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-11-09T13:06:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-09/chelsea-makes-first-profit-since-abramovich-became-owner-in-2003.html
Chelsea made a profit of 1.4 million
pounds ($2.2 million) for the year ended June 30, 2012, the
first time the Premier League soccer club has made a profit
since Roman Abramovich took over as owner in 2003.  Chelsea made the announcement in a statement on its
website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  